ale Projektbeispiele ergänzen die Darstellung.  aInterior design affects the quality of inpatient stay. From the pediatrics unit to the nursing home for dementia patients, patient/"customer" satisfaction is at the heart of the business model for healing and nursing internationally, and is increasingly important in Germany as well. Using the patient room as an innovative springboard, this book offers suggestions and solution approaches for interior design in hospitals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aArchitecturexHuman factors. 0aHealth facilitiesxDesign and constructionxPsychological aspects. 0aHealth facilitiesxPlanning. 0aHospital buildingsxDesign and constructionxPsychological aspects. 0aInterior decorationxPsychological aspects. 0aWaiting roomsxDesign and constructionxPsychological aspects. 4aAlter. 4aEntwerfen. 4aHygiene. 4aInnenarchitektur. 4aKrankenhaus. 4aPatient rooms. 4aPatientenzimmer. 4aage. 4adesigns. 4ahospital. 4ahygiene. 4ainterior design. 70(DE-601)1046537600(DE-588)4032791-7aKrankenhausbau2gnd 70(DE-601)1060941650(DE-588)4072819-5aInnenarchitektur2gnd 7aARCHITECTURE / Interior Design / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2017z9783110547719oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978303821492240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783038211129423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783038211129.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA14ALL  aPDA15STM  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA3STM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DADb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017